#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:2
msgid "Application instance paths"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:4
msgid "The commands that operate with running instances compute instance file paths. Default paths are passed to every instance on start. Other commands use them to communicate with the instance -- for example, to show the logs or connect to the instance through its console socket."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:10
msgid "Path configuration file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:12
msgid "The file ``.cartridge.yml``, located in the application root directory, lets you override default paths for a locally running application. Instead of indicating default paths with flags, you can do so by defining values for similarly named keys in ``.cartridge.yml``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:17
msgid "For example, instead of"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:19
msgid "cartridge start --run-dir my-run-dir --cfg my-instances.yml --script my-init.lua"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:23
msgid "you can write the following in your ``.cartridge.yml``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:25
msgid "run-dir: my-run-dir\n"
"cfg: my-instances.yml\n"
"script: my-init.lua"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:31
msgid "In ``.cartridge.yml``, you can also enable or disable the ``stateboard`` parameter. It is initially set to ``true`` in the template application."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:35
msgid "Directory paths"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:38
msgid "Run directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:40
msgid "The run directory (``--run-dir``) is where PID and socket files are stored. More specifically, it contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:43
msgid "Instance PID files: ``<run-dir>/<app-name>.<instance-name>.pid``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:44
msgid "Instance console sockets: ``<run-dir>/<app-name>.<instance-name>.control``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:45
msgid "Instance notify sockets: ``<run-dir>/<app-name>.<instance-name>.notify``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:48
msgid "Data directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:50
msgid "The data directory (``--data-dir``) contains the instances' working directories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:53
msgid "Each instance's working directory is ``<data-dir>/<app-name>.<instance-name>``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:57
msgid "Logs directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:59
msgid "The logs directory (``--log-dir``) is where instance logs are stored when the instances run in the background. This directory is created on ``cartridge start -d`` and can be used by ``cartridge log``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:63
msgid "Each instance's log file is ``<log-dir>/<app-name>.<instance-name>.log``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:66
msgid "Instance configuration file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/book/cartridge/cartridge_cli/instance-paths.rst:68
msgid "This file (``--cfg``) lets you configure Cartridge instances. The path to the file is passed to all instances as the environment variable ``TARANTOOL_CFG``. See the :ref:`configuration guide <cartridge-config-basic>` for details."
msgstr ""

